
In an afternoon meeting today, FERC extended the price mitigation measures 
for spot markets to all hours, all states in the western U.S. Click below for 
the press release that fully details the Commission order for California and 
the west. This follows the April 26 order to help resolve the energy crisis 
in the west. 

The order is effective immediately upon issue. Chair Hebert said the order 
will be out late tonight or tomorrow. The order was voted out 5-0 with 
concurring opinions by Breathitt, Massey and Hebert. 

http://www.ferc.gov/news/pressreleases/mitigation.pdf

